org.apache.ambari.server.security.authentication.kerberos

Class AmbariKerberosAuthenticationFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.web.filter.GenericFilterBean
      • org.springframework.security.kerberos.web.authentication.SpnegoAuthenticationProcessingFilter
        • org.apache.ambari.server.security.authentication.kerberos.AmbariKerberosAuthenticationFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.servlet.Filter, AmbariAuthenticationFilter, org.springframework.beans.factory.Aware, org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanNameAware, org.springframework.beans.factory.DisposableBean, org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean, org.springframework.context.EnvironmentAware, org.springframework.core.env.EnvironmentCapable, org.springframework.web.context.ServletContextAware

    @Component
 @Order(value=2)
public class AmbariKerberosAuthenticationFilter
extends org.springframework.security.kerberos.web.authentication.SpnegoAuthenticationProcessingFilter
implements AmbariAuthenticationFilter
    AmbariKerberosAuthenticationFilter extends the SpnegoAuthenticationProcessingFilter class to perform Kerberos-based authentication for Ambari.

    If configured, auditing is performed using AuditLogger.

    • Method Detail

      • shouldApply

        public boolean shouldApply(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest httpServletRequest)
        Tests to determine if this authentication filter is applicable given the Ambari configuration and the user's HTTP request.

        If the Ambari configuration indicates the Kerberos authentication is enabled and the HTTP request contains the appropriate Authorization header, than this filter may be applied; otherwise it should be skipped.

        Specified by:
        shouldApply in interface AmbariAuthenticationFilter
        Parameters:
        httpServletRequest - the request
        Returns:
        true if this filter should be applied; false otherwise

      • shouldIncrementFailureCount

        public boolean shouldIncrementFailureCount()
        Description copied from interface: AmbariAuthenticationFilter
        Tests this AmbariAuthenticationFilter to see if authentication failures should count towards the consecutive authentication failure count.

        This should typically be false for remote authentication sources such as LDAP or JWT.

        Specified by:
        shouldIncrementFailureCount in interface AmbariAuthenticationFilter
        Returns:
        true if authentication failure should be counted; false, otherwise

      • doFilter

        public void doFilter(javax.servlet.ServletRequest servletRequest,
                     javax.servlet.ServletResponse servletResponse,
                     javax.servlet.FilterChain filterChain)
              throws IOException,
                     javax.servlet.ServletException
        Performs the logic for this filter.

        Checks whether the authentication information is filled. If it is not, then a login failed audit event is logged.

        Then, forwards the workflow to SpnegoAuthenticationProcessingFilter.doFilter(ServletRequest, ServletResponse, FilterChain)

        Specified by:
